race.description: Mckenzie Ross Insurance Brokers Maiden Plate
race.comment: MISSION OF JOY (9) knuckled down strongly to get within 1.5 lengths of the winner in second last start over 1000m at Mornington on debut. Can measure up again. PRESTIGE STEPHEN (10) finished third, beaten 1.4 lengths, when resuming from a spell last start over 1215m at Kyneton. Hard to beat in this suitable race. TOPMOST (3) is back after a break of five months. At the last run before the layoff he finished fifth over 1400m at Sale. Has trialled two times leading into this. Has ability and is a leading player. DUBAI ADVENTURE (5) boasts the best bloodlines in the field - by the sire of Anamoe and Tentyris out of a former Magic Millions winner - but has been gelded and has hit the line strongly in his past two jumpouts. That's probably how he's going to have to do it here given the wide draw. CHICKY WA WA (7), conversely, showed good speed in a recent easy Avoca jumpout win when he went to line seemingly with something in hand.
